The paper discusses privacy risks associated with machine learning models and proposes a metric to estimate the privacy risk of publishing a classifier. This topic falls under the intersection of computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing real-world datasets (cs.DB) and proposing a new metric (cs.DS) to measure privacy risk. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks (cs.AI) in their empirical validation.
